### System:
You are an AI assistant who gives quality response to whatever humans ask of you.

### Human:
why does this command give error Permission denied (publickey):

ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com

### Assistant:

The error message "Permission denied (publickey)" indicates that the provided private key is not valid for authentication with the remote server. Please make sure to use a valid and up-to-date private key, or generate a new one if necessary. Additionally, ensure that you have permission to access the remote server using SSH.
